issue.title: Properly namespace the picnic internal functions

comment.body: Finally working. @dstebila, I contacted the picnic team. They confirmed their package is the unmodified keccak implementation, so in a 2nd phase we could migrate this to the common folder, but I suggest merging this now to unblock other dependent PRs.

issue.title: Fix list of KEMS to be sent in initial ClientHello
issue.body: The client should by default send a small and fixed number of supported KEMS in its ClientHello. If functionality with additional curves is desired, they can be specified either at compile time or run time.

issue.title: CPU feature copy-and-build from pqclean
issue.body: Together with PR #654 this PR will address issue #624. CI is expected to fail as `copy_from_pqclean` is not run as regular part of the build pipeline. This PR is meant to allow review of the generator scripts. A full PR can be created after running `copy_from_pqclean` (with many more changes caused by the script).
